<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-07T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-07T07:00:00-05:00" n="102" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1098: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the American Delegation
                                        (<persName corresp="#p_GHS1" type="from">Gibson</persName>)
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-07T13:00:00+01:00">June
                                        7, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 7—8:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>233. For the Secretary and the President. Informed in strict
                                confidence by member of the British delegation that they understand
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Sir John Simon</persName> has come
                                out whole-heartedly for <persName corresp="#p_BSA1">Baldwin</persName>’s plan reported in our 169, May 13, 4 p.m.,
                                from London; that the Cabinet was to meet to consider the plan last
                                night and will meet again tomorrow, Wednesday morning, and that it
                                is hoped that the plan will be accepted as a whole for presentation
                                at Geneva. Our informant was not aware of the details of the plan
                                merely knowing that it was of a general character.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>